1	USER DESCRIPTION OF THE PROBLEM

Issue Headline:
Implementation of Oman Arab Bank Payment Interface to ERP

Description:
Oman Air wants to automate the payment processing with Oman Arab bank (H2H integration). Once payment is created and formatted, the payment format file in a predefined csv format will be created and the same will be sent to OAB server. Once the file is received in the landing directory, the file will be parsed for any errors and the successful records will be processed for payments. Error files will be created during payment processing stage and are available for taking appropriate action



2	HEXAWARE UNDERSTANDING OF THE SR

Oman Air wants to automate the payment processing with Oman Arab Bank. Once payment is created and formatted, the format file in a predefined CSV format will be created in a specific directory. This payment file will be transferred to a specific directory in bank server through SFTP transfer protocol.
3	HEXAWARE SOLUTION
1.	After the payment is completed, a new “CSV Payment Format” file will be created as per the format given by OAB. If payment is done to the OAB or any other local bank, then Local CSV format will be used. If payment is for the international bank account, then international CSV format will be used. Payment batch name or quick payment reference will be used to create the CSV file
2.	Once the file is ready, it will be encrypted and then sent to the bank server through SFTP connection.
3.	OA authorized person will login to the OAB portal and approve the payment
4.	Payment file will be processed by bank. If there are any error while processing payments, then errors will be sent to the designated staffs for taking appropriate action
