4	ASSUMPTIONS
1.	If one payment batch contains payment for Local and international banks, then 2 payment files will be created, one for local bank and another for international bank.
2.	Bank will provide the test server to test the automatic file transfer and payment processing
3.	SFTP file transfer is possible between ERP server and the OAB server and vice versa
4.	If Email ID is not available for the vendor, then a default email id will be used (no-reply@omanair.com)
5.	Either Swift code or BIC exists for the beneficiary bank account in ERP
6.	Bank charge type “OUR” will be used.
7.	DFF fields will be provided for Narration1 and Narration2. If these values are not entered while processing payment, then default values (NA) will be used.
8.	In case of any error while processing payment, error will be sent to the OA business team. Payment will be voided in ERP and then re-process the payment after correcting the errors.

